      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KENNYS SON (4) made it two wins and a placing from his last three outings when getting home by 7 metres at Geelong last time out. Came from this barrier to score at Melton last month. Has some speed drawn inside him but he is progressing well so if he can land in the right spot he could strike again. JETAWAY SAINT (1) has yet to feature in three starts since a spell but has come from much wider barriers each time. Fitter for those outings and he has the speed to take advantage of the inside draw so can show his best this time. RYMES (9) drew wide then broke after suffering interference so did well to finish fourth last start at Cranbourne, arriving 4.4 metres behind the winner. Building in fitness and has won here before. AHUNDREDPLUS (8) recorded back-to-back seconds before the last attempt so is worth another chance.",
